{"lemma":"ذُلِّ","slug":"ذُلِّ","root":"ذ.ل.ل","root_slug":"ذ-ل-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ذ-ل-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"ذُلّ","root":"ذلل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n13965","n13971","n13972"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B0%D9%8F%D9%84%D9%90%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be low, to be humble"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"lowness, baseness, vileness, abjectness, meanness, paltriness, contemptibleness, despicableness, ignominiousness, ingloriousness, abasement, humiliation, weakness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"easiness, tractableness, submissiveness, manageableness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gentleness, mercy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the beaten track, part of a road that is well-trodden and even"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun of ذَلَّ (ḏalla)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n13965","headword_ar":"ذَلَّ","root":"*l","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya*il~u","text_ar":"يَذِلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ul~N","text_ar":"ذُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*il~apN","text_ar":"ذِلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*al~apN","text_ar":"مَذَلَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * M, MA, K,) or these three are simple substs., and the inf. n. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~N","text_ar":"ذَلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*alaAlapN","text_ar":"ذَلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ulaAlapN","text_ar":"ذُلَالَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaz~a","text_ar":"عَزَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ul~N","text_ar":"ذُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below;) i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, low, base, vile, abject, mean, paltry, contemptible, despicable, ignominious, inglorious, abased, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weak;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA, Msb, K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haAna","text_ar":"هَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEufa","text_ar":"ضَعُفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a","text_ar":"ذَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~ato","text_ar":"ذَلَّتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb,) aor. as above, (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*il~N","text_ar":"ذِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) said of a man, (M,) and of a beast, such as a horse and the like, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAb~ap","text_ar":"دَابَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":", M, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, easy, tractable, submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manageable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ai*olawolaY","text_ar":"اِذْلَوْلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which belongs to art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*lY","text_ar":"ذلى"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a","text_ar":"ذَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense. (ISd, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu","text_ar":"لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"t*l~l","text_ar":"تذلّل","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He became lowly, humble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he lowered, humbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submitted, himself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*al~aY","text_ar":"تَذَلَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*al~ala","text_ar":"تَذَلَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b3-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a","text_ar":"ذَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said of a road [as meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, beaten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trodden, so as to be rendered even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easy to be travelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to walk or ride upon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aliylN","text_ar":"ذَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tb","text_ar":"تب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~ati AlqawaA fiY li$~aAEiri","text_ar":"ذَلَّتِ القَوَا فِى لِشَّاعِرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rhymes were easy to the poet."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*al~a","text_ar":"ذَلَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"said of a watering-trough or tank, (TA,) or of the upper part thereof, (M,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, broken much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in several places, in its edge, and much demolished."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n13971","headword_ar":"ذُلٌّ","root":"*l","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*il~apN","text_ar":"ذِلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma*al~apN","text_ar":"مَذَلَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[all mentioned in the M and MA and K as inf. ns.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiz~N","text_ar":"عِزٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lowness, baseness, vileness, abjectness, meanness, paltriness, contemptibleness, despicableness, ignominiousness, ingloriousness, abasement, humiliation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"weakness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K. *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa lamo yakuno","text_ar":"وَ لَمْ يَكُنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu waliY~N mina Al*~ul~i","text_ar":"لَهُ وَلِىٌّ مِنَ الذُّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xvii. last verse], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Nor hath"},{"kind":"text","text":"taken to himself"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any aider"},{"kind":"text","text":"to assist Him and league with Him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of any lowness of condition"},{"kind":"text","text":"in Him, as is the custom of the Arabs to do: (K, TA: [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuxAlifuhu","text_ar":"يُخالِفُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuHaAlifuhu","text_ar":"يُحَالِفُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) for they used to league, one with another, seeking thereby to become strong and inaccessible. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aliylN","text_ar":"ذَلِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  And see the paragraph here following, in five places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n13972","headword_ar":"ذِلٌّ","root":"*l","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Easiness, tractableness, submissiveness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manageableness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K, and Ham p. 50; [mentioned in the M and Msb and K as an inf. n.;]) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ul~N","text_ar":"ذُلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K, and Ham ubi suprà.) Hence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoDu Al*~il~i A^aboqaY liloA^aholi","text_ar":"بَعْضُ الذِّلِّ اَبْقَى لِلْاَهْلِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlmaAli","text_ar":"وَالمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Somewhat of submissiveness is most preservative of the family and the property"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboqaY liloA^aholi waAlmaAli","text_ar":"اَبْقَى لِلْاَهْلِ وَالمَالِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ul~u","text_ar":"الذُّلُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad. of Ibn-Ez-Zubeyr; meaning that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abjectness"},{"kind":"text","text":"betiding a man when he bears patiently an injury that has befallen him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is most preservative"},{"kind":"text","text":"of him and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"family and"},{"kind":"text","text":"his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Gentleness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mercy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ul~N","text_ar":"ذُلٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the phrase, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@xofiDo lahumaA janaAHa Al*~ul~i","text_ar":"وَا@خْفِضْ لَهُمَا جَنَاحَ الذُّلِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~il~i","text_ar":"الذِّلِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) in the Kur [xvii. 25, lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And make soft to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"(thy two parents)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the side of gentleness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"treat them with gentleness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the former is the common reading: (TA:) or the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"easiness, tractableness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissiveness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [and so the former, as has been stated above:] Er-Rághib says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~ul~u","text_ar":"الذُّلُّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a consequence of subjection; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~il~u","text_ar":"الذِّلُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is what is after refractoriness: so that the phrase means, [accord. to the former reading,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be gentle like him who is subjected to them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and accord. to the latter reading,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be gentle and tractable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"submissive, to them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beaten track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is trodden and made even,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) of a road. (M, K.) Its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*olaAl","text_ar":"اَذْلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajori AlA^umuwraEalaY A^a*olaAlihaA","text_ar":"اَجْرِ الاُمُورَعَلَى اَذْلَالِهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let events,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs, take their course in the ways,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manners, that are fit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"proper, for them, and easy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) El-Khansà says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"litajori Almaniy~api baEoda AlfataY A@lomugaAdari biA@lomaHowi A^a*olaAlahaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Let fate take its ways after the youth left behind in El-Mahw"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M;) meaning I mourn not for any thing after him: cited by AA: (S in the present art. and in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mHw","text_ar":"محو"},{"kind":"text","text":":)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmHw","text_ar":"المحو"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here the name of a place. (S in the latter art.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^umuwru A@ll~`hi jaAriyapu EalaY A^a*olaAlihaA","text_ar":"اُمُورُ ا@للّٰهِ جَارِيَةُ عَلَى اَذْلَالِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAriyapN A^a*olaAlahaA","text_ar":"جَارِيَةٌ اَذْلَالَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The decrees of God take their"},{"kind":"text","text":"[appointed]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"courses:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) here, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A*lAl","text_ar":"اذلال"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*il~N","text_ar":"ذِلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEohu EalaY A^a*olaAlihi","text_ar":"دَعْهُ عَلَى اَذْلَالِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, in his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[present]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) in this case it has no sing. (M, K.) [And so in the saying,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a EalaY A^a*olaAlihi","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ عَلَى اَذْلَالِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It came in its"},{"kind":"text","text":"[proper]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) ―         -b2-  See also another usage of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*olaAl","text_ar":"اَذْلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a pl. having no sing. assigned to it, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ulo*ulN","text_ar":"ذُلْذُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","M","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}